<TITLE> Assailants kill 1 businessman </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Apr 30 (bdnews24.com) A businessman was killed by assailants at Kalabagan in Dhaka on Friday. The victim, identified as Rokonuddin Babu, 45, was a trader of scrap cloth produced as waste in garment factories (locally called 'jhoot'). Shahin Mondal, OC of Kalabagan Police Station told bdnews24.com that Babu had been chatting with his friends in front of Hamid's CD shop at around 1.30pm. A group of unidentified criminals fired several rounds at him. Babu was hit in the hands, chest and legs. The locals recovered him and admitted him to Shamarita Hospital. The duty doctor declared him dead when he was transferred to Dhaka Medical College hospital. Babu's son Sajib said that the murder might have occurred over his father's business. OC Mondal said that the police was investigating the murder and the motive may be revealed once the investigation was complete. b
